vacancies.description:
Responsibilities:
Expanding the customer base by attracting new customers in the assigned territory;
Developing existing customers in order to increase their share of purchases at Metro;
Actively holding meetings and negotiations;
Informing customers about additional services, programs and promotions;
Consulting customers, introducing them to new types of goods, rules for working with the shopping center;
Interacting with the sales and service departments of the shopping center;
Developing an event to increase sales in the assigned territory.

Requirements:
Sales skills, negotiation skills, high communication skills;
Confident PC skills;
Analytical skills;
Category B license, driving experience from 1 year.

What we offer:
Official employment in accordance with the Labor Code of the Russian Federation;
Official salary;
Five-day work week with two days off;
Traveling nature of the work;
Possibility of professional and career growth in an international company;
VHI policy, the ability to attach relatives to the corporate tariff;
Accident and illness insurance;
A corporate car is provided;
Partial compensation for meals in the corporate canteen;
Additional days of paid leave, additional payment for sick leave;
Discounts on purchases in the Company's Shopping Centers.

Responsibilities:
Development and refactoring of website components of varying complexity (frontend/backend):
frontend: development of a client application based on REST API (javascript)
backend: interaction with the supplier's SAOP API, development of our own REST API (PHP, SQL);
Participation in the full cycle of work related to development: collection and analysis of requirements, design, planning, writing code, its optimization, finding and eliminating errors;
Technical support for clients (interaction with the company's product departments, as well as technical support for subagents on documentation and interaction with the supplier).
Requirements:
Experience with PHP frameworks (understanding of MVC architecture, experience with any of the popular frameworks (Laravel, Yii, Symfony, etc.)
Experience developing in Javascript (knowledge of any of the popular frameworks is welcome)
Ability to work with someone else's code;
Understanding the principles of SOAP / REST API;
Proficiency in basic development tools (IDE, DBMS management, browser developer tools).

We are Wemakefab. We develop websites. We do not work for the flow. We love complex projects, online services, platforms and marketplaces. We focus on functionality and UX.
We believe that employees are the main value of the company. We have been working since 2009 and some specialists have been with us from the very beginning.

We do not have a strict hierarchy and bureaucracy. There is no boss with a club and salary delays.

We work in the center of St. Petersburg and are not against remote work. We are always ready to chat, even if there are no open positions at the moment.

We are expanding and are currently looking for a Frontend developer on Vue (JavaScript) to join our staff for outstaffing projects.

What you will be doing:

Full-fledged website development on Vue.js.
We will be glad to cooperate if you have the following skills and abilities:

good knowledge of JavaScript (ES6), HTML5, CSS;
experience working on Devextreme;
experience working with TypeScript;
experience implementing a microfrontend (Microservices);
have at least 1.5 years of experience developing on Vue.js;

My device is a service for renting devices (electric bicycles, mechanical bicycles, electric scooters, home exercise machines, game consoles, etc.) using a subscription system.
Due to the development of the company and the increase in volumes, we are looking for a specialist who will help make our applications even more convenient for customers.

Main tasks:

Refining the Flutter (Dart) mobile application for Android and iOS;
Implementation of new functionality;
Integration with the back-end (REST API).
